## Jurneys

1. Happy path

1.1 User receives the message -> The PrizeDelivery entity is created -> status =~ PendingDeliveryAdress
1.2 User enters the adress and saves the form (I need a form for this) -> status = PendingDelivery or AdressSet

1.3 The Raffle creator will get a message that the winner has sent him the delivery adress and he has to click a button on this message/form/page that will tirgger a curier delivery call  - the status will be: CurierCalled
The part with the external curier will not be implemented - I need to simmulate this
1.4 Once the curier arrives the Raffle creator will hand over the delivery prize and will mark the prize as Sent from that - this can be done either from the message details page or from the Raffle details page - I need to impleemnt this on both pages  - the status will be: PrizeSent

1.5 This part will be simmulated - the curier part - and we will simmulate that the curier has delivered the prize to the Winnner user - change status to: "PrizeDelivered"
1.6 The user has 2 options now - Accept prize - Reject prize and file a complaint 
For the happy flow he will accept the prize - status = PrizeAccepted
1.7 The Raffle creator will be notified that the prize was accepted and he will get the money in a short time
1.8. The money from the escrow acount will be delivered to the Raffle creator and the Raffle will change the status to Completed - The money transfer part will be simmulated

Basically this is the happy flow


### Breaking points:
1. The user won't provide the delivery details in time
2. The raffle creator will not send the prize in time
3. The Prize is lost on the way - this is handled by the courier - so will be simmulatd in our app
4. The Courier can't find the Ticket winner user - simmulted in our app
5. The Winner user doesn't accept the prize and files a report - this is another path itself - he send's back the prize - The ADMIN need to decide
6. The Winner user doesn't accept the the prize and files a a report but doesn't send back the prize (This is the biggest problem that we can face) - The ADMIN need to decide
7. The winner user doesn't accept the prize and files a report - sends the prize back the prize but the prize is lost by the courier - simmulated - The ADMIN need to decide
8. If we face a situation where the user rejects the prize - the stauts should change to Contested_Prize and the "ball" will be in the Administator's field - He will get a message and need's to decied what to do - in reality the process is much more complex - but in our app we will simmulate that the user can accept the complaint or reject the complaint
8.1 If the ADMIN accepts the complaint - the courier will be called and will send back the prize to the raffle creator(simmulated) and each person who purchased a ticket for that raffle will get thier money back - the Raffle status will be - Failed/Rejected_prize
8.2 If the ADMIN reject's the complaint the courier won't be called and the prize will remain at the winner ticket's user - The money will be sent than to the raffle creator that will be notified and the Raffle will change it's status to "Completed"


## Summary
 Happy flow - user accepts prize


Negative flows:

1. User rejects prize 
- outcome 1: ADMIN confirms complaint - REJECTED_PRIZE raffle -> money restored
- outcome 2: ADMIN rejects complaint - COMPLETED raffle  -> money goes to raffle creator
2. User does not fill delivery details
3. Raffle creator does not send the prize
4. Courier not deliver prize in time - "lost on road" --> Delivery company problem
5. Courier does not find the ticket winner user at adress / phone number
6. User rejects prize but does not return the prize
7. Courier does not return the prize to Raffle creator if user rejection was accepted --> Delivery company problem
8. Courier returns the prize but does not find the Raffle crator
